<DIV2 N="1" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>The First Chapiter.</HEAD>
<P>_O Yee false Heartes / 
yee Ypocrites / together
with all yee presumpteous
vnsent Teachers / Wherfore
do yee thus trouble and mo|lest
the Littleones / and the
single-minded Elect of God / 
for to withdrawe them with your false and vnclene
Doctrine of the goodthinking Knowledg / from the
Single-mindednes which they haue to the pure
Doctrine of the Seruice of the Loue of <HI>Iesu Christ:</HI>
and so to leade them away and to estraunge them / 
from the mercifull Grace of our heauenlie Father&punc;
from the Safe-making of our Lorde <HI>Iesu Christ<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter"></HI>
<PB REF="6">
and from the Loue of the Holie-gost / whervnto they
haue humblie &amp; obedientlie geeuen-ouer themselues.</P>
<P>2. Woe vnto you and your Presumption / yee
false and seducing Spirites. yee sathanish Houndes
and renting Wolues. yee Generations of Vypers
and <HI>Cains</HI> Ministers. Yea woe vnto you, yee
Nestes of Dragons and Habitations of Deuels / 
together with all yee wicked Heartes of the Scrip|ture-learned:
For yee and your Fathers haue be|trayed
Gods Propheates&middot; as also <HI>Iesu Christ</HI>
and his Witnesses. hauing falslie accused and de|famed
them: and euenso &lsemicol;through the Handes or
Power of Sinners; persecuted and killed them.</P>
<P>3. O Thou wicked Nature / and yee Childre~
of <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">nbeleef / which forsake the Purging
in <HI>Iesu Christ</HI> / through the Beleef / and the vpright
Beeing of the Loue of <HI>Iesu Christ,</HI> and expell the|same
out of your Heartes / together with the Ac|complishing
of the true Oblation or Godseruice in
the Holie / to the Slaying and Burying of your
Sinnes / and to the Renewing of your Spirit and
Minde: Is it not Wickednes and Euel-fact e|nough
for you / that yee haue turned-away your|selues
from the Requiring of y^e Loue and her Ser|uice
/ and from the faithfull Sheepe or Children of
thesame&middot; made your Portion with the Goates&middot; pol|luted
yourselues in all Vnbeleef / contrarie to the
Safe-making of our Lorde <HI>Iesus Christ</HI> and his
holie Spirit of Loue&middot; prepared you to Vessels of
the Wrath of God&middot; and &lsemicol;with your false Iudg|mentes
and Blaspheaming of the Holie-gost; pluc|ked
vpon your owne Neckes / the dreedfull Iudg|ment
and wrathfull Woord of the Lorde <HI>[Depart
<PB REF="6">
from mee / yee Curssed, into the euerlasting
Fire / which is prepared for the Deuell and his
Angels or Messengers]</HI> But that yee must also
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">with your false Doctrine and vncleane Lippes;
pursue and persecute the Elect <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">the faithfull Childre~
of the Loue of <HI>Iesu Christ<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">,</HI> for to robbe them of
their Inheritaunce of the Kingdom of God and of
the Loue of <HI>Christ,</HI> to holde them captiue in your
damnable Beeing or Estate / and that yee mought
make them partakers with you and all wicked Spi|rites
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">if it were possible that yee could seduce them;
of your Damnation.</P>
<P>4. For verelie / till vnto thesame Iudgment of
this your Condemnation / yee are <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">O yee Children
of the Deuell / and Members of <HI>Antichrist;</HI> helde
bound with the Bandes or Chaines of Darknes / 
to thende that the God of Heauen should <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">in this
Daye of his righteous Iudgment; make-manifest
and bring his Vengeaunce ouer you / to your Re|compencing
with the Fire of Hell.</P>
<P>5. Yea / euen-thus will the God of Heauen pre|sentlie
in this Day / openlie bring-fourth and make-knowne
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">before your Eyes / and before all Eyes of
Vnderstanding; the Hardnes of your Heartes / 
with your Lyes &amp; Blaspheaminges of God / which
yee haue spoken against God the Father and his
mercifull Grace&punc; and against <HI>Christ</HI> and his Righ|teous-making
from the Sinne&punc; as also against the
holie Spirit and his Making-aliue in the Loue.</P>
<P>6. Euen-thus will presentlie in this Day of the
righteous Iudgment of God <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">O yee presumpteous
Blaspheamers of the Holie-gost and his Familie
of Loue; all the Woe of the Vngodlie com ouer
<PB REF="7">
you / to your Rewarding.</P>
<P>7. FOr-that-cause looke now into your Abho|minations
/ and marke how yee haue sepe|rated
yourselues with y^e Goates / from the Sheep / 
with the which yee shall also (if so be that yee do not
whollie turne you away therfrom / and repent) be
constrained to beare your Sentence of Condemna|tion.
Therfore looke now rightlie into it / and re|pent
/ ereuer the Vengeaunce of God fall vpon you.
Yea looke well into it / how yee haue madevp your|selues
with your false Iudgmentes / against God-his
righteous Iudgment / and against the holie
Spirit of the Loue of <HI>Iesu Christ,</HI> and his Com|munialtie
of Holyones: In such wise / that yee haue
also indeuoured you / to seduce God-his elected Ho|lyones
/ and to make the gratious Woorde <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">which
God hath raised-vp by vs / according to his Pro|mises;
and the Ministers of thesame Woord / hor|rible
and despised / before all Goodwillingones to
the Righteousnes: and so then to pluck them away
from the Communialtie of Loue / and to leade them
with you <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">in your Chaines or Bandes of Darknes;
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">nto Damnation / to thentent that they should not
by any-meanes be taught <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">through the Obedience
of the Seruice of Loue; to the Kingdom of Heauen / 
which yee shuttoo before Many / and com not ther|in
yourselues<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter"> but that they should remaine with
you / ther-without.</P>
<P>8. Yea euen-thus / with your Falshod and for|ged
Lyes / and with your subtile Slaunders and
flattering Woordes / yee com-fourth so knowledg|full
/ and occupie also <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">according to the Similitude
or Figuring-fourth of the Scriptures; such a co|loured
<PB REF="7">
Shew of Christianitie / for to leade-astraye / 
that yee should <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">if it were possible; seduce also the
Elect / with your false or coloured Christianitie.</P>
<P>9. But no: Yee are not able in this Daye of
Loue / to seduce the Elect / nor to accomplish your
Seduction, with the Holyones of God of the Fa|milie
of Loue: For y^e liuing God of Heauen <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">which
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">s their God&punc; and their Defender from all Seduc|tion;
goeth so stedfas<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">lie <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">in his Seruice of Loue;
with his true Light of the heauenlie Cleernes of <HI>Ie|su
Christ</HI> / before them all which are his faithfull
Childre~ of Loue / and geeueth them daylie <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">through
his holie and gratious Woord; such a cleere Di|uersitie
in their Heartes: and the true Light of all
the Righteous and Holyones of God / is so naked|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">ie
distincted vnto them / from the Darknesses of the
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">alse Light of all y^e Vnrighteous / and false Heartes
of the Scripture-learned or of the vnsent Pr<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">ach|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">rs / 
That it is not possible that yee should seduce
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">hem (if they holde them constantlie on the Ser|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">ice
of Loue) from the Waye of the Loue of <HI>Iesu
Christ:</HI> nether-yet that yee should be able <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">yee wic|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">ed
Generations of <HI>Cain,</HI> and yee false Prophetes
of <HI>Iezabel;</HI> to destroy or keep-back in them / Gods
Trueth and Righteousnes.</P>
<P><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">0. Verelie our Lorde and Sauiour / <HI>Iesus
Christ,</HI> hath well and rightlie spoken and prophe|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">ied
of your subtile Falshod and dec<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">itfull Signes
and Wonders for to leade-astray: In such wise / 
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">hat the Elect should also <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">if it were possible; th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">ough
your subtile Falshod and loftie Knowledg / 
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">elead into Errour.</P>
<P><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">1. But for the Elects-sake / the Dayes are now
<PB REF="8">
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">hortened: For God will presentlie in this Day <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 word">
his Loue &lsemicol;in y^e which Hee will keep his Iudgment
execute his righteous Iudgment: and will euen<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="2 letters">
glorifie his Elect / in his Righteousnes or Perfec<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">tion / 
and make them ioyfull &lsemicol;with his euerlastin<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
Li<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">e; in his Kingdom of Heauens: as also mak<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
manifest all false Deuices which are practi<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">ed for <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 word">
leade-astray: and condemne you / with the Vngod<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">lie
and Blaspheamers of the holie Spirit of Loue
and with all Children of the Deuell / in the Hel<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
where-as &lsemicol;in the beholding of their Vngodlynes
all Woe / Wringing-of-handes / and Gnashing <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 word">
Teeth shall take-holde of them / euerlastinglie.</P>
<P>12. FOr-that-cause ought eueryone to look
well to it / what hee iudgeth for euell an<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
blaspheameth: and to haue a good regarde on th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
Matiers which concerne God or his Seruice / fo<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
to vnderstand those-same first well and aright / ac<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">cording
to the Trueth / ereuer hee iudg them for e<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">uell / 
and slaunder or despise them. For it will con<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
very heauelie vpon them / which stretch-out the<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
Handes to Gods Sanctuarie / for to take-holde <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 word">
thesame with vncleane Handes / and to resist an<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
blaspheame &lsemicol;with vncleane Heartes / and with vn<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">circumcised
Tunges and Lippes; Gods Work<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
with his Holyones or Children of Loue.</P>
