<DIV2 N="2" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>The Second Chapiter.</HEAD>
<P>OH &lsemicol;alas; how many-maner <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 word">
false heartes are ther now! which do <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 word">
&lsemicol;eueryone with hys craftie Knowledg<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
makeup themselues against God and <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 word">
<PB REF="8">
Seruice of Loue / and are not ashamed to spew|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">urth
their horrible Lyes &amp; Blaspheamies against
Gods gratious Woord and his Seruice of Loue.</P>
<P><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">. And then cometh fourth the one Partie from
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">he one syde&punc; and the other Partie from the other
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">yde / vnto the Goodwilling to the Loue of <HI>Iesu
Christ,</HI> and saye vnto them: <Q>Yea as I heare / yee
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">ade also the Bookes of the Familie of Loue / which
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="2 letters">re setfourth by <HI>HN:</HI> Hee writeth <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">verelie; many
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">xcellent Matiers / wherin hee resiteth much of the
Loue / and teacheth Men <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">ther-withall; to the vp|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">ight
Beeing of <HI>Christ:</HI></Q></P>
<P><Q>But what is that to the purpose: Ther lyeth
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">reat Falshod hidden ther-vnder: wee knowe what
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">ee haue found-out by thesame. Therfore take yee
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">eed therof / and looke well to it / that yee be not se|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">uced
therwith&punc; nor drawen to y^e Familie of Loue.
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 word"> warne you of the horrible Seduction / and of the
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">rronious Bookes of <HI>HN:</HI> to thend that yee be not
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">lucked with the Familie of Loue / into horrible Er|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">urs.</Q>
And so they do then spew-fourth many for|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">ed
Lyes / and beas<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">lie Matiers / wherwith they do
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="2 letters">cuse and defame the Familie of Loue&punc; as also <HI>HN</HI>
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">nd the Elders which minister the holie and graci|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="2 letters">s
Woorde / in the Familie of Loue / for to make
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">enso with their false Defamations / the Familie
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 word"> Loue / wherin God liueth and walketh&punc; together
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">ith <HI>HN</HI> God-his elected Minister<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter"> and the El|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">ers
in the Familie of Loue / horrible and despised
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">fore all People.</P>
<P><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">. Beholde / such venemous Foode of Death
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">ontrary to the wholsom Foode of Life and of the
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">rueth of God; can the Deuell prepare / through
<PB REF="9">
his Ministers and Ministrices / and through <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 word">
false Heartes of the Scripture-learned / and <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 word">
Ministers of the false Godseruices of <HI>Cain:</HI> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 word">
they knowe then how to couer thesame Falsho<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
vnder a Shew of Holynes and of Loue which th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
beare vnto Men / to thend that they should not fa<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
to fulfill the Measure of the Iniquitie of their F<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="2 letters">thers / 
and that the Dayes which reach to the<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
Condemnation / mought be shortened.</P>
<P>5. WOe vnto you / yee false Heartes: <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 word">
presentlie in thys Daye shall all yo<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
Lyes and forged false Testimonies <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">which yee yo<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
selues haue made very filthie / with your vnclea<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
Dirt; be condemned in the hellish Fire: For th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="2 letters">same
your false Testimonies are brought-four<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
out of the earthlie Ingeniousnes and Generat<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="2 letters">
of the Deuell: and yee haue exalted yourselues <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 word">
your earthlie Ingeniousnes; so hie / with thesam<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
and with the Workes of the Fleash / to a great E<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">timation
with Men / and planted your false Se<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
so fast in the Heartes of Men / that yee haue vtte<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
lie expeiled ther-out the God of Life / the safe-maki<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
<HI>Christ,</HI> and the Holy-gost of the heritable Rich<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
of the h<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">ouenlie Bewtie&punc; also lead many men <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 word">
vnto Des<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">ruction&punc; and brought many in<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">o gre<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
Heauynes and greeuous Miscrie: and haue eue<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
so ther-through / prepared the Iudgment of yo<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
Condemnation / the-sooner ouer yourselues.</P>
<P>6. Therfore shall also presentl<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">e <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">through <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 word">
your Fall; many vpright Heartes be able ligh<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
to perceaue / that yee are thesame Messengers of <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 word">
Deuell / which are gon-fourth against God and <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 word">
Seruice of Loue / and against his Trueth / for
<PB REF="9">
seduce <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">with your vncleane Dirt and painted Ho|lynes;
the simple Heartes / fro~ the Familie of Loue
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">like-as yee haue don vnto many other ignorant
Men / which walke without the Howse and Ser|uice
of Loue; and to pluck them into your Snares.
But verelie it shall not auaile you in this Daye of
Loue / by the Faithfulones of the Familie of Loue / 
to spread-abrode your seducing Seedes any far|der.
For your false Practises&punc; and your Fall / are
now well perceaued of the vpright Heartes.</P>
<P>7. Yea consider well theron <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">O yee goodwilling
Heartes to the Righteousnes; how slylie these
Messengers of the Deuell com vnto you. this
Broode of <HI>Lucifer.</HI> these Resisters of the Trueth / 
as <HI>Iannes</HI> and <HI>Iambres.</HI> these false Ministers of
the Priestes-office / as <HI>Nadab</HI> and <HI>Abihu.</HI> these
Seditious-persons / as the Company of <HI>Chore.</HI>
and these vnsent bloud-thirstie Preachers / as the
Priestes of <HI>Iezabel:</HI> Consider (I saye) aduisedlie
theron / how subtillie they shew-fourth themselues / 
and can paint their false Nature / with an Angels-colour / 
to thentent that one should not perceaue the
Falshod of their wicked Heartes&punc; and the Lustes
and Desires of their Whordom and Adulterie / 
wherof their Eyes and Heartes are full: and that
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">hey mought euenso vnder a coloured Couering / 
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">loke their Vncleannes of Whordom and Adulte|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">ie / 
together with their abhominable Idolatrie and
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">alse Godseruices&punc; as also lay those-same their Ab|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">ominations
and Vncleannes / vpon the Neckes
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">f the Single-mynded and Good-willingones to
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">he Loue of <HI>Iesu Christ,</HI> or report such-thinges of
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">hem&punc; and so accuse and defame them therwithall.</P>
<P><PB REF="10">
8. BEholde / yee that haue Eyes for to per|ceaue
/ such false Heartes and contentious
Deuels-messengers / which seeke not the Peace o<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
<HI>Christ</HI> nor the Concorde in the Loue. but bring-i<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
all Renting and Dissention or Breach / are driuen-fourth
by the false Spirit of <HI>Antichrist,</HI> and by th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
lying Ingeniousnes of the Fleash / for to practise al<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
Deceit and Falshod / according to the Workes <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 word">
the Deuell / and also to seduce the simple single-min<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">ded
Heartes / like-as they do the Vnfaithfull and
Waueringones in the Beleef / vnto their Errour.</P>
<P>9. And if then the Deuell cannot accomplish o<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
bring thesame to-passe <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">at full; through his Belia<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">lish
Men / so bringeth hee thesame also into th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
Handes of the false Women / which are inclined t<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
such wicked Workes / and haue cra<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">tie Subtiltie
to accomplish the false Deuices of the Deuell.</P>
<P>10. Euen-thus verelie / do they all deale wit<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
Deceit and Falshod / which go-out from the wicke<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
World: and also all those which h<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">ue geeuen the<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
thervnto. And so doth eueryone of them diligentli<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
applye him / to sowe euery-where his Mischeef an<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
contentious Seedes. and to spew-fourth all Blas<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">pheamie / 
against God and his Familie of Loue.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="3" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>The Third Chapiter.</HEAD>
<P><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">Hy on you / yee whorish Genera<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">tions
and adulterous Children of the vn<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">cleane
and defiled Bed: How are yee thu<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">seeing that yee yourselues are so vnclen<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
growen to such Presumption! that yee com vn<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="2 letters">
the Elect of God and Children of Loue / and <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 word">
<PB REF="10">
vpon you as also indeuour you / for to mingle your
Vncleannes of the Hedghogs-filthines and Swi|nes-dung / 
among our pure and heauenlie Foode / 
or to bring it in besides thesame / and to feede our
sweet-hearted Children of the Loue ther-withall / 
like as yee haue don / towardes the Vnfaithfull and
vnto many Worldlie-mynded. Phy / phy on the
stincking Dirt of your Vncleannes.</P>
<P>2. Verelie / like as the Dirt of your Vncleannes
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">s a filthie Stinck before God / euenso is it also a fil|thie
Stinck in our Noses.</P>
<P>3. And although yee garnish thesame your stinc|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">ing
Dirt <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">when as yee bring thesame vnto vs;
with Roses and Lillies / and with many-maner of
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">aire Flowers / and strew it ouer with Rosemary|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">eaues
and Cinamon / yet doth neuerthelesse the
Sunne of Righteousnes <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">with his bright &amp; whot
Shyning; make the Stinck of thesame / manifest
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">efore vs. Yea so manifest / that all those that haue
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">ynded the Loue and her Seruice / with vpright
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">nd faithfull Heartes / and shewe all Obedience
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">owardes thesame / haue a great Lothsomnes of the
Stinck of thesame Dirt.</P>
<P><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">. For the holie and gratious Woord of God / 
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">hich is heald-fourth before vs in liuing Power
through the holie Spirit of y^e Loue of <HI>Iesu Christ,</HI>
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">nd through God-his elected Minister <HI>HN;</HI> in the
Seruice of Loue / and which is <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">as the true Bread
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">f Life / that is com vnto vs from Heauen; admini|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">red
to a liuing Foode of our Soules / is so reue|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">nd
and so godlie for vs to heare and to feed-of / 
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="2 letters">d wee haue also turned our Lust and Loue so
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">hollie thervnto / that wee abhor and haue a great
<PB REF="11">
Lothsomnes / to heare of any-thing els. Yea and
much-more a Lothsomnes / to receaue or inioy any|thing
of any straunge Spirites / or of anyone which
is a Straunger vnto the Familie of Loue.</P>
<P>5. THerfore / seeing that <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">ee com not fourth
out of the Familie of Loue / nor haue not
Gods Woorde nor Spirit / in liuing Power by
you. but onlie the Imaginatio~ of your Knowledg / 
or the dead Letter / which all false Heartes of the
Scripture-learned / occupie to Contention and Di<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">|corde:
So bide then hardelie with your garnished
Dirt / by yourselues: For heere by the Faithfull
and Electedones in the Familie of Loue / it is al-to-well
knowne.</P>
<P>6. But if yee desire to repent / and to com by vs
in Sorrowfulnes <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">or your Sinnes / for to be con|uerted
and made-sa<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">e from all your Abhominati|ons&punc;
and taught and instructed aright / in the Way
of the Trueth of <HI>Iesu Christ:</HI> and so then to liue
vprightlie in all Trueth of God and <HI>Christ:</HI> So
forsake it then all that yee haue taken to you / with|out
the gratious Woorde of God and the Requi|ring
of his Seruice of Loue / and seperate you whol|lie
therfrom: and assemble you than euenso to our
Communialtie of Sainctes / to Vnitie of Heart in
the Loue / so shall yee then be receaued of vs with
Ioye: And thus in y^e Repentaunce / let yourselues
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">vnder the Obedience of the Loue and her Seruice<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
be wasshed and cleansed from all your Sinnes / 
with the holie and pure Waters of the holie Spirit
of Loue: and be than taught with the pure Doc<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">trine
of y^e holie and gratious Woord / to the King<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">dom
of the God of Heauens / and nourrished-vp <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 word">
<PB REF="11">
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">ncient Elders and Fathers of the Fa<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">ilie of
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">oue; in the holie and godlie Vnderstanding / to
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">end that yee mought knowe and obserue / all that
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">hich pleaseth God / and is resonable and edifying
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">ith Men&punc; also confesse and publish-fourth the safe-<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">aking
Beleef of <HI>Christ</HI> and his vpright Fruites
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 word"> Righteousnes&punc; and out of thesame Treasure of
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">ur Heartes&punc; rightlie bring-fourth <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">out of the true
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">oue o<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter"> <HI>Iesu Christ;</HI> the New and the Olde / to a
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">od Instruction of other moe.</P>
<P>FOr-that-cause <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">according to the Counsaile
of the holie Scripture; becom yee No<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">rned-about to obedient Childre~ / and borne anew / 
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="2 letters">t of the Water and out of the Holie-go<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">t: and
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 word"> then <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">as new-borne Children; the pure vncor|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">pted
Milke / out of the virginlie Breastes of the
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">oue: To thend that yee mought euenso after-that
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">hen-as yee are entred into the Begining of the
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">ristian Doctrine&punc; and nourrished-vp to y^e Young|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">anship
of the holie Vnderstanding; be fead with
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">e strong Meate of the gratious Woorde&punc; and
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">nd by the Holie-gost of Loue / into all Trueth and
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">haritie.</P>
<P>Thus haue a good and right regarde vnto
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">e Sentences of the Wisdom / and receaue the|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">me / 
to the Renewing of your Vnderstanding / 
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">nd to Goodwillingnes to the vpright Righteous|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">s:
and indeuour you not first / to pluck-out the
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">plin<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">er out of anothers Eye / ereuer yee haue plu<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">+<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">d
the Beame out of your owne Eye. Nether-yet
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">plye you also to be a Teacher / so long as the
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">octrine to the Kingdom of Heauen / is yeat need|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">ll
for yourselues.</P>
<P><PB REF="12">
9. Applye you not also to liue / nether-yet <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 word">
shew or witnes the Life vnto another / ereuer th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
yee yourselues are passed-thorowe the Death&punc; an<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
gon-thorowe the small Waye which leadeth vn<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="2 letters">
Life.</P>
<P>10. Likewise take not vpon you / to euangeli
the <HI>Euangelie</HI> of the Kingdom vnto anyman / e<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">cept
that yee haue in the Obedience of the Requ<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">ring
of the Loue / receaued the Kingdom of Heaue<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
seene with your Eyes <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">in the vpright Beeing
<HI>Christ;</HI> the Life which is euerlasting&punc; heard th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
same <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">in y^e Renewing of your Spirit and Mind
with your Eares&punc; and handled or felt it <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">in the v<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
right Righteousnes &amp; Holines; with your hande<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter"></P>
<P>11. Also speake not of any Mysteries of God <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 word">
his Kingdom / except that yee haue so learned th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
same Mysterie / in the Seruice of Loue / and that
be profitable for to be declared &amp; fruitfull to hear<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
and stretch to all Concord / Peace / &amp; Righteousnes<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter"></P>
<P>12. Likewise take not vpon you to minister an<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
Seruices of <HI>Christ,</HI> nor to witnes or preach t<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
Knowledg of <HI>Christ</HI> according to the Spirit / e<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="2 letters">cept
that yee haue first obedientlie fulfilled the Se<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="2 letters">uices
of <HI>Christ</HI> and his Doctrine / and that <HI>Chri<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="2 letters"></HI>
haue his Shape in you: and that euenso <HI>Chri<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="2 letters"></HI>
himself / speake thesame Testimonies through you<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter"></P>
<P>13. Fardermore / be not diligent to teach t<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
Trueth vnto anyone / except that yee haue first b<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
obedient vnto the Trueth and her Requiring&punc; <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 word">
are taught by the holie Spirit of Trueth / in t<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
Seruice of Loue&punc; as also knowne to be meet a<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
ordained by the Elders in the holie Vnderstandi<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
of the Trueth / to the Ministration of the True<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="2 letters"></P>
<P><PB REF="12">
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">e not also blowen hether-and-thether with
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 word"> Windes or Spirites which rule in the Ayre / 
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">ther suffer yourselues to be driuen / by the Spi|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">es
of Knowledg / which haue their Working in
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 word"> Children of Men which knowe not God / nor
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">t their trust in Him.</P>
<P>But ground and stablish you on the euerlast|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">g
fast-standing Foundation of <HI>Iesu Christ:</HI> and
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">sider in your Vnderstanding / that yee are in
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">th-wise called vnto <HI>Christ</HI> / through the holie <HI>Eu|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">gelie</HI>
of <HI>Christ,</HI> for to haue an vpright Beeing
<HI>Christ,</HI> and so then to buyld vpon Him.</P>
<P>THus let eueryone looke well to it / and
holde a sharp Watch ouer himself / that
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 word"> be not lead-astray by his owne Knowledg / so
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">ll hee not then also seduce an other. But let eue|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">one
hold himself obedientlie on the pure Doctrine
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">he gratious Woord and Seruice of Loue: For
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">oso letteth not himself obedientlie / be taught and
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">ected to the true Light of the euerlasting Life / vn|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="2 letters">
the Doctrine of the gratious Woord and Ser|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">e
of Loue / nether-yet dealeth and walketh faith|fullie
vnder the Obedience of Loue / hee shall
not be able to teach or leade other right|lie.
but they shall <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">like-as y^e Blinde
which leade each-other; fall
together into the Gulf
or Pit of Destruc+tion.</P>
<TRAILER>Take it effectuallie to heart.
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">HARITAS EXTORSIT PER ABIA.</TRAILER>
